@startuml
|User|
start
:Clicks the "Forgot password" option in the Login Page;

|System|
:Generates a password recovery form;

|User|
:Writes the registered email address;
:Submits the request by clicking the "Recover password" button;

|System|
:Sends a query to verify whether the email exists in the database;

|Database|
:Returns the query;

|System|
:Verifies the email exists in the system;

if (Does the email exist in the system?) then (yes)
    :Generates a password recovery token associated with the User account;
    :Sends a request to the configured email service to deliver a password recovery email containing the reset link;
else (no)
    |User|
    :Sees an error message on the Login Page indicating that the email is not registered;
    stop
endif

|Email Service|
:Sends the password recovery email containing the reset link;

|System|
:Verifies whether the recovery email was sent successfully;

if (Was the recovery email sent successfully?) then (yes)
    |User|
    :Sees a confirmation message on the Login Page indicating that the recovery email has been sent;
    :Clicks on the recovery link received by email;
else (no)
    |User|
    :Sees an error message on the Login Page;
    stop
endif

|System|
:Generates the password reset screen;

|User|
:Sees the password reset screen;
:Writes a new password;
:Submits the new password;

|System|
:Validates the new password;

if (Is the new password a valid password?) then (yes)
    :Sends a query to update the password in the database;
    |Database|
    :Updates the password;
    |System|
    :Confirms the password was updated successfully;
    |User|
    :Sees a confirmation message indicating that the password has been updated;
    stop
else (no)
    |User|
    :Sees an error message on the password reset screen asking to enter another password;
    stop
endif
@enduml